    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Power Cylinders - Clean, Inspect,
        and Measure - Measure Piston Rings
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="measure" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Measure Piston Rings</title>
        <figure id="f3350015460" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh04/H04006.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Piston ring end gap measurement</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The top of a piston can be used to push piston ring down in the cylinder sleeve to insure ring is
                    squarely positioned in the sleeve.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install each piston ring into its cylinder bore. Make sure the ring is perpendicular to the
                cylinder wall. If measuring used rings, install ring just below the top of piston ring travel.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_394.xml" xrefid="t335001503">feeler gauge</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335001503"/>
                to measure the end gap between the ends of each piston ring.
            </para>
            <para>Discard any piston ring that does not meet
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_T335001501.xml" xrefid="t335001501">Specifications</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335001501"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>If any piston ring is replaced, replace all piston rings and the cylinder sleeve for that
                    cylinder.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
